  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "F&B EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p>As an <strong>F&B Executive</strong>, you will help run the day-to-day operations of our food & beverage outlet. This role is hands-on and involves supervising staff, ensuring smooth service, maintaining food quality, and supporting management to achieve sales and operational goals.</p><p>You will act as a bridge between management and frontline staff, making sure operations run efficiently and customers have a good dining experience.</p><h2><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h2><h3><strong>Daily Operations</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Oversee daily outlet operations to ensure smooth service</p></li><li><p>Ensure food and beverages are prepared and served according to company standards</p></li><li><p>Handle customer feedback and resolve issues professionally</p></li><li><p>Ensure cleanliness, hygiene, and food safety standards are met at all times</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Staff Management</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Supervise, guide, and motivate service and kitchen staff</p></li><li><p>Assist in staff scheduling, attendance tracking, and manpower planning</p></li><li><p>Train new staff on service standards, food handling, and workplace rules</p></li><li><p>Ensure staff follow company policies and SOPs</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Stock & Cost Control</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Monitor inventory levels and assist with ordering supplies</p></li><li><p>Reduce wastage and control food and operational costs</p></li><li><p>Check deliveries and ensure correct quantity and quality of items received</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Sales & Performance</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Support promotional activities and upselling initiatives</p></li><li><p>Monitor daily sales and assist in basic reporting</p></li><li><p>Help achieve outlet sales targets and improve efficiency</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Compliance & Safety</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with NEA, MOM, and workplace safety regulations</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper documentation and cleanliness records</p></li><li><p>Report any operational or safety issues to management promptly</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h2><h3><strong>Experience & Skills</strong></h3><ul><li><p>At least <strong>1–2 years of experience in F&B operations</strong> (supervisory experience is an advantage)</p></li><li><p>Basic knowledge of food hygiene and safety standards</p></li><li><p>Ability to lead and work well with a team</p></li><li><p>Good communication and problem-solving skills</p></li><li><p>Customer-oriented with a positive attitude</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Personal Traits</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Responsible, reliable, and hands-on</p></li><li><p>Able to work under pressure in a fast-paced environment</p></li><li><p>Willing to work shifts, weekends, and public holidays</p></li><li><p>Physically fit for standing long hours</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Education</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Food Hygiene Certificate is preferred (training can be provided)</p></li></ul>",
